%N A265273 Least positive real z > 2/5 such that 1/2 = Sum_{n>=1} {n*z} / 2^n, where {x} denotes the fractional part of x.
%C A265273 This constant is transcendental.
%C A265273 The rational approximation z ~ 34988721583274868054335940408411507283/85070591730234615865843651857942052860 is accurate to many thousands of digits.
%C A265273 This constant is one of 6 solutions to the equation 1/2 = Sum_{n>=1} {n*z}/2^n, where z is in the interval (0,1) - see cross-references for other solutions.
%C A265273 The complement to this constant is given by A265274.
%H A265273 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/DevilsStaircase.html">Devil's Staircase</a>.
